<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ul>
            <li><code class="language-text">indexName</code>&#160;<b>(required)</b>: the name of the local secondary index. The name must be unique among all other indexes on this table.</li>
            <li><code class="language-text">keySchema</code>&#160;<b>(required)</b>: the key schema for the local secondary index.<ul><li><code class="language-text">hashAttributeName</code>&#160;<b>(required)</b>: the name of the partition key.</li><li><code class="language-text">rangeAttributeName</code>&#160;<b>(required)</b>: the name of the sort key.</li></ul></li>
            <li><code class="language-text">projection</code>&#160;<b>(required)</b>: specifies attributes that are copied (projected) from the table into the index. These are in addition to the primary key attributes and index key attributes, which are automatically projected. Each attribute specification is composed of:<ul><li><code class="language-text">projectionType</code>&#160;<b>(optional)</b>: specifies which kinds of attributes are projected into the index. Valid values are <code class="language-text">KEYS_ONLY</code>&#160;(only project the index and primary keys), <code class="language-text">INCLUDE</code> (project the index and primary keys as well as other non-key attributes), and <code class="language-text">ALL</code> (project all table attributes).&#160;The default value is <code class="language-text">ALL</code>.</li><li><code class="language-text">nonKeyAttributes</code>&#160;<b>(optional)</b>: an array of non-key attributes which will be projected into the index. You can specify between 1 and 20 non-key attributes in a single secondary index. You can specify up to 100 non-key attributes across all local and global secondary indexes on a particular table (duplicate non-key attributes are counted multiple times).<ul><li><code class="language-text">attributeName</code>&#160;<b>(optional)</b>: the name of this particular non-key attribute</li></ul></li></ul></li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>